---
@@aREMORT@@W
Your @@yfirst@@W remort class requires the matching mortal
pre-requisite class at @@y100@@W.
Your @@ysecond@@W remort class requires:
  - your first remort class at @@y100@@W,
  - all mortal classes at @@y100@@W, and
  - the matching mortal pre-requisite class for that second remort
    at @@y100@@W.
When you are ready to remort, type gain <first three letters of new class>.
Remort classes and mortal pre-requisites are:
        -@@pSorcerer@@W (Mage)
        -@@WWizard@@W (Mage)
        -@@aPaladin@@W (Cleric)
        -@@CPriest@@W (Cleric)
        -@@dAssassin@@W (Thief)
        -@@dWarlock@@W (Thief)
        -@@cKnight@@W (Warrior)
        -@@cSwordsman@@W (Warrior)
        -@@GNecromancer@@W (Psionicist)
        -@@mEgomancer@@W (Psionicist)
        -@@gMonk@@W (Pugilist)
        -@@gBrawler@@W (Pugilist)

@@aADEPT@@W
Adept classes are a third tier of progression beyond remort. To unlock
adepts, you must have at least @@y2@@W remort classes at level @@y100@@W.
Each adept class requires both of its matching remort classes at @@y100@@W.
When you are ready to adept, type gain <first three letters of adept class>.
Adept classes and their remort pre-requisites are:
        -@@pGrand Magi@@W (Sorcerer + Wizard)
        -@@aTemplar@@W (Paladin + Priest)
        -@@dNightblade@@W (Assassin + Warlock)
        -@@cCrusader@@W (Knight + Swordsman)
        -@@GKinetimancer@@W (Necromancer + Egomancer)
        -@@gMartial Artist@@W (Monk + Brawler)